# Architecture Rules

## Layer Dependencies
- `entity` depends on nothing (only stdlib)
- `usecase` depends on `entity` and repository interfaces
- `repository/sqlite` depends on `entity` and `database/sql`
- `handler` depends on `usecase`, `entity`, `chi`
- `cmd/server` wires everything together

## Adding a New Entity
1. Create `internal/entity/<name>.go` with struct + `Validate()` method
2. Add sentinel errors to `internal/entity/errors.go`
3. Define interface in `internal/repository/interfaces.go`
4. Implement in `internal/repository/sqlite/<name>.go`
5. Add migration in `internal/repository/sqlite/migrations.go`
6. Create usecase in `internal/usecase/<name>.go`
7. Create handler in `internal/handler/<name>.go` with `Routes()` method
8. Mount in `cmd/server/main.go`
9. Add seed data in `internal/repository/sqlite/seed.go`

## Error Handling
- Repository returns `entity.ErrNotFound` for missing records (not `sql.ErrNoRows`)
- UseCase validates before calling repository
- Handler maps errors to HTTP status codes via `writeError()`

## Database
- SQLite with WAL journal mode, 5s busy timeout, foreign keys ON
- MaxOpenConns=1 (SQLite single-writer)
- Migrations are idempotent (CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS)
